rComments: Very good professor. The course is not hard if you go to class and read the book. He is a very nice teacher and seems to make sure his students get the material, especially if they show any interest in it.
This guy seriously looks like he's 20. And his exams are pretty easy. Just read the chapters and you will be fine. I know a lot of people who studies 4-5 hours before the midterm and gets 80+.
Teacher is great. Although he's a bit older now compared to the last rating he got, but he still decent at what he does. his exams are tricky but if you study you should be alright.

Good Prof :) It's good having a professor that's young and energetic~ the funny thing is.. he'll say a long sentence, then he suddenly stops, stares at the crowd with a hand in the blackboard and a raised eyebrow~ HAHAHHAHAHAAHA~

he's young which is a good change from the old geezer profs. he really goes by the book which is awesome because if you go to class and do the readings, you'll be a pro...and if you have to miss class for something you can easily get back on track by going through the text on your own.

I had this guy for micro. It wasn't bad. He does read from the book a lot though. You could miss a course and just read from the book instead and you wouldn't be worse off. But he's a nice guy. He plays videogames which is cool in my book! :D

This class is sooo boring! My goodness, this man loves nouns! he will give you the same situation literally ten times in a row and simply switches the noun. Half of the class stopped coming to class three weeks in because he READS the textbook. He is a really nice guy though. He is very democratic about choosing exam dates too. :)
